FBIS4-21856 "jptot015__l94021" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 13 April 1994 LATIN AMERICA GUATEMALA Roundup of Guerrilla Activities Roundup of Guerrilla Activities PA0704222994 PA0704222994 BFN [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of reports on Guatemalan guerrilla activities monitored through 4 April. Corporal Julio Perez Guajaca and soldier Antonio Garniga Bolvito, members of a military patrol, were killed in a clash with guerrillas of the Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity on 31 March in Playa Grande, El Quiche Department, the Army reported on 3 April. The Army also reported that URNG guerrillas burned down a bus on the road leading to La Libertad, El Peten Department because the driver refused to pay "war taxes." (Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 4 April 94 p 119)
